 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucazickaacee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CazicKaacee</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 9:15:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: overcrowding</span><hr size=1> Well, the added random spawn timers have slowed respawn, leading to more 'downtime' and more competition for spawns.  So, I'd suggest they drop at least a day off of every uber respawn that is currently over four days.  Thus, more raid content, and less competition over spawns and exp areas, and a more enjoyable game.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I'm pretty disgusted with Everquest at this time.  Making things rare is good, but the high level population outrageously outnumbers the possible uber targets on most nights, leading to a few nights of fun raiding, and a bunch of days of downtime until respawn or a patch.  Thus, while Everquest was designed as a cooperative game, the high level game is more about competition between the high level guilds. <p><img  SRC="http://members.home.net/aszura/test.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugnomified.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gnomified</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 9:43:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: overcrowding</span><hr size=1> What I don't understand at all is why Verant doesn't take a proven design - KC, for example - and duplicate it.  A gnoll castle deep within Blackburrow.  Requires a key that an NPC directly outside the zone line gives when a player says &quot;I need a key&quot; (level..  45 minimum).  Make it an indoor zone but increase either the drop rates or make the items a little better than what drops in KC.  (to compensate for the indoor flag)  The layout of KC is very nice, since it's easy to learn.  It would still be easy to escape a zone like KC with or without SOW, so the fact that it would be indoor should not turn people away.  (especially with better loot)<br>
<br>
The only problem is duplicating the zone.  They would have to have a few significant changes, obviously - but why change it too much?  Run a storyline about a gnoll that dabbles in wizardry and visited KC.  He loved it and decided to create his own castle and fashion it after what he remembers of KC. *shrug*  <br>
<br>
Not only would we get another decent zone for grouping, but it would bring people to that side of the world.  The only other surefire way to bring people to this zone would be add a zoneline between NK and the gnoll castle.  A little tunnel that would take you into what would be the sewers area.  If they did that, I am sure the zone would certainly be worth it and that lots of people would try it out.<br>
<br>
I guess they tried something like this earlier, with that zone that was supposedly the new LOIO - and they placed it near Erudin, to try and bring people that way.  I've never been there, so I can't comment on it, but I assume they didn't get it right for whatever reason.<br>
