 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uabsolutemaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Absolute Master</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/02 9:53:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://stuwww.kub.nl/~s338419/everquest/gohan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: overcrowding</span><hr size=1> I don't really see the problem here unless you want to get gimped exp and are too lazy to try something different.  The problem tends to be a lot bigger with older and more populated servers (Dang on my server 30 people in Seb is considered packed to the brim and is usually empty, 40 for Velk) but really it's only a problem if you don't bother to look elsewhere. Great alternative zones outside of KC, Seb, Velk.<br>
<br>
HS -&gt; Best exp in the game here ( a group of high level players doing south wing - east wing crawl to DS will net you a ton of exp even at 60). It's my favorite zone in the game.<br>
<br>
The Hole -&gt; People complain about the pathing and how there is no good loot, yet the experience here is the only thing that rivals HS (deeper in). Had a group go in fought all the way down to Yael's room and fought the way back up without a cleric and no deaths. A crawl like that netted great exp and great fun (especially when fighting 5 golems and some adds at once). After you get passed the low blue and green elementals and get in the city and lower, you will see the exp rake in. As long as you dont touch the walls, you're fine<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Chardok -&gt; Another very underrated zone (on my server the word is out about the great exp and usually has 20-30 people these days). Most people stay at camps like the fort, observer and capt. While this will give out ok exp, the key to Chardok is to crawl and never stay at one spot too long. Get your group and get as far deep as you can. Tons of fun and all the groups that I've brought there or got into were amazed at how great the exp is and became hooked on Chardok instantly. Korocaust room is good exp also, nets a good challenge and you can get nice items. My favorite camp is Treasury.<br>
<br>
DN -&gt; Very though zone but if you have a well balanced group with lots of damage you can get pretty far deep in the rat caves. Most groups I've been in there would go as deep as they can until they wipe or evac. Lots of risk, but loads of fun and a lot of nice item drops.<br>
<br>
SG -&gt; Never considered this an exp zone. Mobs have too much HP and there just isn't much motivation in fighting there unless you go deep in to farm some rare quest gems.<br>
<br>
Grieg's End -&gt; Raid zone, absolutly no exp to be had here as low blue mobs and greens have ton of hitpoints, hit extremely hard, are usually unslowable and unmezzable, and a crawl means death. Tried it a couple of times, after a small excursion, CR'ed and went to Akheva.<br>
<br>
Akheva -&gt; Moderate to good exp. This is another zone that can push the limits of your group. Right path leads to mindwurms that give fair exp and net some good hybrid spells, the north path gets hard quickly for one group but you can try to move up until the difficulty is just right and stay in that room. No loot, just exp.<br>
<br>
The Grey -&gt; Nerfed to hell. Awful exp in a group. Leave to the quad kiters to play with.<br>
<br>
Acrylia -&gt; AE group territory. It's still good exp for a single group though.<br>
<br>
Maiden's Eye -&gt; Good outdoor pick up zone, as long as you don't stay at the dawnshroud zone which is kinda silly and stupid at the same time. Akheva or umbral plain zone line are good places as long as the umbral toilers in one of the corners near the little castle/fort.<br>
<br>
Umbral Plains -&gt; Mostly a raid zone but again a good group can handle a lot of things in here. Average exp.<br>
<br>
Kael -&gt; Iceshard keep or if you're group can handle it Arena. Not the greatest experience, but faction help and some Thurg drops.<br>
<br>
Fungus Grove -&gt; Try the caller quest sometime. Usually a nice change from just killing shrooms all day.<br>
<br>
Cazic Thule -&gt; Extremely tough. If your group can manage it though, the exp per mob is great. Did a crawl with one group up to 3rd floor of 4c before we had to leave.<br>
<br>
There are others I probably missed but notice that the secret to good exp is to crawl a dungeon in most cases. Most of these zones I mentioned yield much better exp then Velk ever did. The smart people never actually go from zone to zone and sit at the zone line trying to get a group in a zone with 50-60 people. The last time I ever did a lfg shout in a zone was at level 54 and never go in zones. I put up my lfg tag do my regular business in ec or solo somewhere and wait for the good group offers. This may seem easier for an enchanter, but it works for any class (I always pick out people for groups doing that). This is how people get to do these other zones. You also save yourself the aggravation of not doing anything at all when lfg and will have much more fun in your group then just staying in your camp spot and hope to get one of the spider pops before one of the other groups steals it.<br>
<br>
